diff --git a/docs/api/structures/user-agent-metadata.md b/docs/api/structures/user-agent-metadata.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000..8a23272379
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/api/structures/user-agent-metadata.md
@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@
+# UserAgentMetadata Object
+
+* `brands` [UserAgentBrandVersion](user-agent-brand-version.md)[] (optional) - Brand/version pairs used for low-entropy `Sec-CH-UA` values and `navigator.userAgentData.brands`.
+* `fullVersionList` [UserAgentBrandVersion](user-agent-brand-version.md)[] (optional) - Brand/version pairs used for high-entropy full-version Client Hints values.
+* `fullVersion` string (optional) - The full browser version used when Chromium exposes the legacy full-version Client Hint.
+* `platform` string (optional) - The platform token used for `Sec-CH-UA-Platform` and `navigator.userAgentData.platform`.
+* `platformVersion` string (optional) - The platform version used for high-entropy platform-version Client Hints values.
+* `architecture` string (optional) - The CPU architecture token used for high-entropy architecture Client Hints values.
+* `model` string (optional) - The device model token used for high-entropy model Client Hints values.
+* `mobile` boolean (optional) - Whether Chromium should expose the mobile User-Agent Client Hints value.
+* `bitness` string (optional) - The CPU bitness token used for high-entropy bitness Client Hints values.
+* `wow64` boolean (optional) - Whether Chromium should expose the Windows-on-Windows 64-bit Client Hints value.
+* `formFactors` string[] (optional) - Form factor tokens used for high-entropy form-factor Client Hints values.
