+#### `contents.setUserAgentOverride(options)`
+
+* `options` [WebContentsUserAgentOverrideOptions](structures/web-contents-user-agent-override-options.md)
+
+Overrides the user agent and User-Agent Client Hints metadata for this
+`WebContents`. The override applies to frames and dedicated workers created
+after the call.
+
+Call this API before `loadURL()` when the override must apply to the first
+navigation. Shared workers and service workers use the session-level or app-level
+override because they are scoped to a storage partition rather than a single
+`WebContents`.
+
+#### `contents.clearUserAgentOverride()`
+
+Clears this `WebContents` user agent override and restores the current
+session-level or app-level fallback for future navigations.
+
 #### `contents.getUserAgent()`
 
 Returns `string` - The user agent for this web page.
